      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PHOENIX RED (8) struggled in tougher grade last start after settling off pace at this track, but prior to that won by 2 lengths at this track (22.17) beating Time To Prophet in a Grade 5 on March 4. Remains without a win from the draw but has been in the placings two times from three attempts. Has claims if he runs up to expectations. ASTON CHANT (5) had a tricky draw and ran well to finish second, beaten 0.8 lengths, (22.43) at Warrnambool. Expected to be in this for a long way. PAW NELLY (2) has been beaten for early speed lately, last time finishing fourth (22.98) in a Restricted WIN at Geelong. Has a strong record here at this journey including two wins. Has ability and is one of the better chances. KEY BEGONIA (1) with some luck can improve on an unplaced run last time here.",
